National Security Advisor Susan Rice met with UN High Commissioner for Refugees Antonio Guterres to discuss the humanitarian crises in Africa and the Middle East. They talked about the needs of refugees and conflict-affected individuals and emphasized the global responsibility to respond to these crises. They also discussed new approaches to support host countries dealing with long-term refugee situations. Rice highlighted the important role of UNHCR and other UN agencies in addressing these crises and pledged ongoing U.S. support.